Laptops are becoming increasingly powerful every year thanks to the steady release of more power-efficient processor and GPU technologies. Portable devices with great performance are also becoming cheaper due to the increased availability of solid state drives and the capabilities of modern chips. While some gaming laptops have retained their large form factors in favour of using the most powerful hardware available, many manufacturers have opted to combine slim, portable chassis with cutting-edge hardware. New and impressive features found within modern laptops include OLED displays, SLI graphics cards, overclockable processors, and even secondary touch screen displays. We have listed the top eight laptops you can buy in South Africa, based on reviews from around the web and the availability of local hardware at the time of writing. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-283938" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Dell-XPS-13.jpg" alt="Dell XPS 13" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Dell-XPS-13.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Dell-XPS-13-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Dell-XPS-13-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-238790" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/HP-Spectre-x360.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/HP-Spectre-x360.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/HP-Spectre-x360-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/HP-Spectre-x360-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-